From: Li Nan <linan122@huawei.com>
Date: Mon, 22 May 2023 15:25:34 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] md/raid10: fix wrong setting of max_corr_read_errors
Git-commit: f8b20a405428803bd9881881d8242c9d72c6b2b2
Patch-mainline: v6.5-rc1
References: git-fixes

There is no input check when echo md/max_read_errors and overflow might
occur. Add check of input number.

Fixes: 1e50915fe0bb ("raid: improve MD/raid10 handling of correctable read errors.")
Signed-off-by: Li Nan <linan122@huawei.com>
Reviewed-by: Yu Kuai <yukuai3@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Song Liu <song@kernel.org>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20230522072535.1523740-3-linan666@huaweicloud.com
Signed-off-by: Coly Li <colyli@suse.de>

---
 drivers/md/md.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/md/md.c b/drivers/md/md.c
index 2fc8d25f6e80..49c83ed08937 100644
--- a/drivers/md/md.c
+++ b/drivers/md/md.c
@@ -4468,6 +4468,8 @@ max_corrected_read_errors_store(struct mddev *mddev, const char *buf, size_t len
 	rv = kstrtouint(buf, 10, &n);
 	if (rv < 0)
 		return rv;
+	if (n > INT_MAX)
+		return -EINVAL;
 	atomic_set(&mddev->max_corr_read_errors, n);
 	return len;
 }
